<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="199" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1538,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,1538,1564]" pageId="3" pageNumber="199">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. Forewing radial fork with branches diverging at an angle of about 30°. Epiproct rounded at apex; hypandrium with a narrowed ridge medially. Female. Forewing radial fork with branches diverging at an angle of less than 90°; cells r3 and r5 almost hyaline; basal area with irregular hyaline areas. Pigmented area of subgenital plate roughly T-shaped, nearly pointed at apex; dorsal valve anterior one-third with a small slightly sclerotized area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
